-- Hungary's Budget Draft Includes Industry `Crisis' Tax Income Through 2014
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2010-11-10T09:01:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/hungary-s-budget-draft-includes-industry-crisis-tax-income-through-2014.html
Hungary’s 2011 budget plan includes
revenue projections from a special tax on selected industries
through 2014, according to the budget draft posted on
Parliament’s website.  Hungary estimates revenue of 348 billion forint ($1.8
billion) in 2011, 260 billion forint in 2012 and 179 billion
forint each in 2013 and 2014. This includes taxes on financial
institutions as well as industry taxes which currently apply to
energy, retail and telecommunication companies.  The government earlier said the tax would be in place from
2010 to 2012.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  